Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

## 1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` in your page

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            // Don't await — fire and forget since the method returns bool
            ShowUnsavedChangesDialog();
            return true; // Cancel default navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async void ShowUnsavedChangesDialog()
    {
        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
            await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

> **Note:** `OnBackButtonPressed` handles the hardware/system back button (Android back gesture, etc.). It does **not** intercept the Shell navigation bar back arrow.

## 2. Custom "Cancel" back button in the toolbar

Replace the default back arrow with a custom toolbar item:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage"
             Shell.BackButtonBehavior="{x:Null}">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

## 3. ViewModel command handling the confirmation

```csharp
public partial class EditProductViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Back()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "Discard changes and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave) return;
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

## Key points

| Concern | Solution |
|---------|----------|
| Hardware back button (Android) | `OnBackButtonPressed()` → return `true` to cancel |
| Shell nav bar back arrow | `BackButtonBehavior` with custom `Command` |
| Custom button text | `TextOverride="Cancel"` |
| Programmatic navigation | Check unsaved state before calling `GoToAsync("..")` |

The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` fully replaces the default back navigation, so you own the entire flow — show a dialog, then navigate only if confirmed.
